\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 13. D. anatolicus }Boiss.,{\i  Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov.}{\b  1}({\b 1}): 22 (1843). Caespitose perennial 8-35 cm. Leaves 1-1·8 mm wide, linear, acuminate. Flowers solitary or 2 or 3 together; pedicels 5 mm or more. Epicalyx-scales (4-)6, narrowly ovate, apiculate. Calyx 8·5-11 mm; petal-limb 2·5-3·5 mm, linear to linear-oblong, subentire to dentate, white. {\i Turkey-in-Europe} ({\i Gelibolu peninsula}). Tu. ({\i Anatolia.})
\par 

