\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. D. pulviniformis }Greuter, {\i op. cit.} 189 (1965). Dwarf shrub forming rounded hummocks. Leaves of young branches 1-1·5 cm, needle-like, densely crowded. Flowering stems 3-5 cm, slender, 2- or 3-flowered. Epicalyx-scales c. ½ as long as calyx, with slender mucro 1-1·5 mm. Calyx 7-8 mm. Petal-limb 3-4 mm wide, obovate, cuneate, shortly and sharply dentate, white.{\i  Limestone rocks, c.} 600{\i  m. • S. Kriti} ({\i Kedros}). Cr.
