\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 18. D. rupicola }Biv.,{\i  Sic. Pl. Cent.}{\b  1}: 31 (1806). Small shrub 30-60 cm. Leaves 3-5 mm, wide, rather thick, linear-oblong, the lower obtuse, the upper acute. Flowers in bracteate heads; pedicels short. Epicalyx-scales 12-16, obovate, acuminate. Calyx 25-30 × 4-5 mm, almost cylindrical. Petal-limb 10-15 mm, dentate, bearded, pink.{\i  S. Italy, Sicilia, Mallorca.} Bl It Si.
