\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 19. D. fruticosus }L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 413 (1753) ({\i D. arboreus} auct., non L.). Small shrub up to 50 cm, with tortuous branches. Leaves 3-8 mm wide, linear to oblanceolate or elliptical, obtuse, fleshy, glaucous. Flowers numerous; pedicels short. Epicalyx-scales (8-)10-20, obovate, shortly cuspidate. Calyx 18-25 × 2-3 mm, narrowed from about the middle. Petal-limb c. 10 mm, dentate, bearded, pink. 2n = 30.{\i  S. & W. Greece, S. Aegean region.} Cr Gr.
